> There's nothing better in life than hearing those three little words: bacon, lettuce, tomato. Crispy, salty, juicy, and slightly sweet—the classic combo is as simple as it is satisfying. Think it couldn't get any better? Hold onto your hats, because our chefs took the best parts of a BLT and a cheeseburger and combined them to create the world's greatest dinner mash-up. Everything is sandwiched between buttery brioche buns with a swipe of lemony, herb-flecked aioli. On the side, there's crispy seasoned potato wedges and Caesar-dressed mixed greens with toasty almonds. Talk about a dinner dream come true!

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}. Mince @Chives{1/4%ounce}; place in a #medium bowl{}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Slice @Roma Tomato{1} into rounds; place in a separate medium bowl with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, @Fry Seasoning{1}, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, place @Almonds{1/2%ounce} in a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Toast, stirring often, until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Return same pan to medium-high heat and add @Bacon{4%ounce}. Cook, turning occasionally, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Turn off heat; reserve bacon fat. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, add @Mayonnaise{6%tablespoon}, garlic, and half the @Italian Seasoning{1/2%tablespoon} to bowl with chives; stir to combine. Add lemon zest and lemon juice to taste; season with salt and pepper.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, remaining @Italian Seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}, pepper, and @Salt{3/4%tsp}.

Form mixture into two patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun. Season with salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings: Use 1 1/2 tsp salt. Form mixture into four patties.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon} (or reserved bacon fat) in pan used for bacon over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top each patty with @Gouda Cheese{2%slice}. Cover pan to melt cheese.

While patties cook, halve and toast @Brioche Buns{2}.

Reserve a handful of @Mixed Greens{2%ounce} for topping burgers. Toss remaining mixed greens in a second large bowl with @Caesar Dressing{1.5%ounce}, @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup}, and toasted almonds; season with salt and pepper.

Spread a thin layer of aioli onto cut sides of toasted buns. Fill buns with patties, seasoned tomato, bacon, and reserved mixed greens.

Divide burgers between plates along with potato wedges and remaining aioli. Serve with salad and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.